# Why: Bulk replace user-facing "Documenso" copy in apps/remix routes +
#      components — page titles, share metadata, completion CTAs, signup
#      terms-of-service URLs, signature-disclosure articles, etc. ~30
#      string substitutions across 17 .tsx files.
#
#      Substitutions applied (most-specific first):
#        1. "Documenso, Inc."  → "BizRethink AI"
#        2. "Documenso Logo"   → "Pacta Logo"
#        3. "Documenso License" → "Pacta License"
#        4. Standalone "Documenso" → "Pacta"
#
#      URL substitutions (manual edits):
#        - https://documen.so/terms   → https://bizrethink.ai/terms
#        - https://documen.so/privacy → https://bizrethink.ai/privacy
#        - admin@documenso.com (placeholder) → admin@bizrethink.ai
#
#      Files INTENTIONALLY skipped (admin-only / suppressed surfaces):
#        - root.tsx (license-expired banner, suppressed via overlay 005)
#        - admin-license-card.tsx, admin-license-status-banner.tsx
#          (suppressed via overlay 005)
#        - organisation-billing-banner.tsx (billing disabled in our build)
#        - meta.ts (already covered by overlay 022)
#
#      Tooling: see /tmp/rebrand-routes.py for the substitution script.
#      Re-run it after upstream merges to catch new "Documenso" mentions.
#
#      Translation catalogs (packages/lib/translations/*.po) are regenerated
#      separately via `npm run translate:extract`. They auto-pick up the new
#      source strings; manual .po edits would be lost.
#
#      Fragility: MED. This is the largest patch surface — 17 files. Upstream
#      is most likely to add new "Documenso" mentions here when they ship
#      new features. The substitution script is idempotent so re-running it
#      after a sync resolves new conflicts cleanly.
